EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Land Use Call-Up be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle:
By Council Member Johnson:
Pursuant to Rule 11.20(b) of the Council and §20-226 or §20-225 of the New York City Administrative Code, the Council resolves that the action of the Department of Consumer Affairs approving an unenclosed sidewalk café located at 356 West 44th Street, Borough of Manhattan, Community Board No. 3, Application No. 20165009 TCM shall be subject to review by the Council.
EventItemMatterName: Zoning, Sidewalk café, 356 West 44th St, Borough of Manhattan (20165009 TCM)

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Land Use Call-Up be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle:
By Council Member Chin:
Pursuant to Rule 11.20(b) of the Council and §20-226 or §20-225 of the New York City Administrative Code, the Council resolves that the action of the Department of Consumer Affairs approving an unenclosed sidewalk café located at 221 West Broadway, Borough of Manhattan, Community Board No. 1, Application No. 20165108 TCM shall be subject to review by the Council.
EventItemMatterName: Zoning, Sidewalk café, 221 West Broadway, Manhattan (20165108 TCM)

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Land Use Call-Up be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle:
By Council Member Barron:
Pursuant to Rule 11.20(c) of the Council Rules and Section 197-d(b)(3) of the New York City Charter, the Council hereby resolves that the action of the City Planning Commission on Uniform Land Use Review Procedure (ULURP) application no. C 150318 PQK be subject to Council review.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the revocation, suspension, or refusal to renew a cigarette dealer license due to the sale of synthetic drugs or imitation synthetic drugs
EventItemMatterName: Revocation, suspension, or refusal to renew a cigarette dealer license due to the sale of synthetic drugs or imitation synthetic drugs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to identifying and addressing environmental justice issues
EventItemMatterName: Identifying and addressing environmental justice issues.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to banning the sale of green lasers in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Banning the sale of green lasers in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the removal of inoperative or decommissioned fire hydrants
EventItemMatterName: Removal of inoperative or decommissioned fire hydrants.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the suspension of parking meter regulations on days that New York City public schools are closed because of inclement weather
EventItemMatterName: Suspension of parking meter regulations on days that NYC public schools are closed because of inclement weather.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the retention of data on the open data portal
EventItemMatterName: Retention of data on the open data portal.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: Resolution condemning the inequitable contract between the City of New York and LinkNYC which will provide better Wi-Fi access to areas throughout the City where advertising is deemed more profitable, and calling for revenue sharing profits from this contract to be invested in efforts to increase Wi-Fi access in the Bronx, Brooklyn, Queens and Staten Island.
EventItemMatterName: Condemning the inequitable contract between NYC and LinkNYC which will provide better Wi-Fi access to areas throughout the City.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to introduce and pass legislation to allow states and municipalities to expand upon the Food and Drug Administration’s nutritional labeling requirements on menus and menu boards
EventItemMatterName: Congress to introduce and pass legislation to allow states and municipalities to expand upon the FDA’s nutritional labeling requirements on menus and menu boards.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to notifying a business when the city has received a request for service or complaint about its operation.
EventItemMatterName: Notifying a business when the city has received a request for service or complaint about its operation.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation that would allow limited liability companies formed in New York to fulfill their publication requirement by publishing on the New York Department of State’s website or on an online news site
EventItemMatterName: Allow limited liability companies formed in NY to fulfill their publication requirement by publishing on the NY Dept of State’s website or on an online news site.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to locating electrical conductors underground.
EventItemMatterName: Locating electrical conductors underground.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to require the department of citywide administrative services to conduct a survey of city contractors in relation to paid family leave policies
EventItemMatterName: Conduct a survey of city contractors in relation to paid family leave policies.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A.7938 / S.5056-A, an act that would authorize the city of New York to institute a tenant rent increase exemption program for tenants who pay over fifty percent of their incomes in rent and who reside within certain rent-regulated properties
EventItemMatterName: Authorize NYC to institute a tenant rent increase exemption program for tenants who pay over fifty percent of their incomes in rent and who reside within certain rent-regulated properties. (A.7938 / S.5056-A)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to opportunities for LGBT-owned business enterprises in city procurement
EventItemMatterName: Opportunities for LGBT-owned business enterprises in city procurement.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to penalties for electronic waste littering
EventItemMatterName: Penalties for electronic waste littering.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to include a check box on school lunch forms to enable parents to indicate whether they want regular or vegetarian meal options for children during the school year, and requiring DOE to continually update their forms if any other options are offered in the future.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to include a check box on school lunch forms to enable parents to indicate whether they want regular or vegetarian meal options for children during the school year.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Education Department to expand the State’s financial literacy and personal finance education curriculum to all grades K through 12.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Education Dept to expand the State’s financial literacy and personal finance education curriculum to all grades K through 12.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A.7272/S.5823-A, in relation to increasing the minimum gross registered vehicle weight requirement for tow trucks to decrease illegal tow truck chasing.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing the minimum gross registered vehicle weight requirement for tow trucks to decrease illegal tow truck chasing. (A.7272/S.5823-A)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.8186-A/S.5886-A, an act to amend the General Business Law and the Vehicle and Traffic Law, in relation to the transfer of motor vehicles as scrap.
EventItemMatterName: Transfer of motor vehicles as scrap. ( A.8186-A/S.5886-A)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to opportunities for disabled-owned business enterprises in city procurement
EventItemMatterName: Opportunities for disabled-owned business enterprises in city procurement.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to expand vegetarian lunch menu options for students at New York City public schools.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to expand vegetarian lunch menu options for students at NYC public schools.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget
EventItemMatterName: Approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety

EventItemMatterName: Declaring nuisances related to the sale of synthetic drugs and imitation synthetic drugs.

EventItemMatterName: Requiring a data dictionary for every data set on the open data portal.

EventItemMatterName: Procedures and reporting for the Rikers Island nursery program.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the standardization of address and geospatial information on the open data portal
EventItemMatterName: Standardization of address and geospatial information on the open data portal.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature and the People of the State of New York to amend the State Constitution, and the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation amending the Election Law to establish same-day and online voter registration.
